This directory contains the source code for the FISH Oracle database API.

Copyright (c) 2011-2013 Malte Mader
Copyright (c) 2011-2013 Center for Bioinformatics, University of Hamburg

All Java source code is deposited in src/de/unihamburg/zbh/fishoracle_db_api.
Following refered to as src/.

src/lib/                   JUnit and MySQL libraries
src/data/                  Source code for all objects storing data fetched
                           from the database.
src/driver/                Source code for adaptor objects fetching the data
                           from the database.
src/test/                  JUnit unit tests.
src/util/                  Source code for database connection and data encyption.
testdata/                  Contains testdata in CSV format.
emtpyoracle.sql            Contains the database structure for the FISH Oracle
                           database.
data.sql                   Contains some useful sample/basic data.

BUILDING THE API
--------------------------
In the root directory of source tree, run

  ``ant'' or
  ``ant compile''      to compile the code
  ``ant test''         to run the unit tests
  ``ant jar''          to build a JAR-file containing the classfiles
  ``ant clean''        to remove all compiled binaries.
  ``ant cleanup''      to remove all compiled binaries and jar file.
